@node read "Intro:"
                                     Intro:


         Basically this is a tool where you can set Listviews to hold as
                          many Lines of text you need.
              you double click the ListItem to set the Clipboard.

 Then you can press the Right_Amiga-V to Paste the text into anywhere possible

     This was originally written For AmIRC to be able to store preset Texts
         (Like it's FKey Settings) and Paste into the window with ease.

Now i've added a few features like ..

Prefs file argument to load a different config at startup.
Prefs files can be Dropped on Clipper Window

A cycle gadget lets you cycle to different lists (Unlimited Pages)
if pages go beyond Screen height popup Cycle won't popup but will cycle

Open a Textinput_mcc Edit Window to configure Clips (IRC Mode)

Open a Textinput_mcc ReadOnly view Window to see your clip with the real
output rather than seeing special control Characters (colours/bold)

Bubble Helps are set :)

Hide/Show/Rearange  Image Icons in main window

Added German/French Catalogs (: will add more :)

Change the clipboard Unit Number and set Default Min/Max Unit


Saving Settings Saves ...
   Current Page position.
   If an item is selected this is remembered and auto pasted at each startup.

Also take a minute to read @{" Important things to know: " link imp}

@endnode

@node imp "Important things to know:"


                           Important things to know:
                            -------------------------

   For AmIRC if AmIRC is already running and you don't have Clipper installed
       you will have to reload in order to see Clipper.amirx in the Menus


                                     ALSO.

                         this program is Currently Beta

 I use it Often, so any bugs I find will be fixed (please report any YOU find)

@endnode

@node runing "Running Clipper"


                                Running from WB:


      Just double click the icon to load/create s:ClipPrefs/Clipper.cfg :)



                               Running from CLI:

               Currently there is only 1 arg that can be supplied

                          Syntax:  Clipper <filename>

           if filename is omited then S:ClipPrefs/Clipper.cfg is used

@endnode
@node use "Usage"


                                     Usage:


                   Double Click a text to set the clipboard.

               Select the 'Edit' Gadget or menu to edit the clips

       Select the 'GUI Prefs' Gadget or menu to edit the program Settings

       For more detailed info see @{" Prefs " link prefs} for how to configure

@endnode

@node prefs "Configuration"

                              Configuring Clipper


       Saving prefs also saves the selected page, Selected List position
                             and GUI configuration.

            To UN-Select a ListItem before saving prefs i have added
                    an Un-Select MenuItem (Ramiga - <minus>)

    Use the 'Edit' menu or the small image to Hide/Show Edit Window/gadgets

         Selecting 'Edit' opens a new editing window and makes visible
                     some extra gadgets on the main window.

       the selected Clip is displayed in the Edit window and here you can
                     edit the name and the text of an item.


ABOVE the main window Cycle gadget are 5 small gadgets..

the first 2 (left) move a list item up or down,
the 'A' is for Adding a new Clip to the bottom of the list,
the 'I' is for inserting a New Clip into the current positon
the 'R' is for Removing the selected Clip

BELOW the Cycle gadget are 5 more gadgets the same and a String gadget..

The String gadget is for changing the name of the current 'Page'
the other gadgets work the same as the ones above but they will
affect the Pages (Cycle gadget)


                   It's All pretty straight forward really :)

              Bubble help Is all you should need to understand :)

                                  have a play


@endnode

@node hist "The Story so far"

 History
